00:10:10,850 --> 00:10:13,420
it’s like he tried
to dive under the ambulance.

257
00:10:13,450 --> 00:10:14,960
woman: I feel
responsible for this.

258
00:10:14,990 --> 00:10:16,890
I know there’s no excuse
for what happened,

259
00:10:16,930 --> 00:10:19,430
but I didn’t have a chance
to restrain him.

260
00:10:19,460 --> 00:10:21,460
Jotaro: Life can be bizarre.

261
00:10:21,500 --> 00:10:24,470
man 2: He was pinned
between the asphalt and tire.

262
00:10:24,500 --> 00:10:26,700
The force tore off his face.

263
00:10:26,730 --> 00:10:27,870
( Officer 1 clears throat )

264
00:10:27,900 --> 00:10:30,670
do we know
the identity of the victim?

265
00:10:30,710 --> 00:10:34,480
Woman: He was yoshikage Kira.
He told me his name himself.

266
00:10:34,510 --> 00:10:36,480
- ( All gasp )
- Officer 1: Kira.

267
00:10:36,510 --> 00:10:39,950
There’s an old house in kotodai
belonging to the Kira family.

268
00:10:39,980 --> 00:10:41,750
I heard there was
only one occupant,

269
00:10:41,780 --> 00:10:43,320
so he might not have family.

270
00:10:43,350 --> 00:10:44,690
Koichi: An accident.

271
00:10:44,720 --> 00:10:47,320
To think an accident
would end this.

272
00:10:47,360 --> 00:10:49,290
rohan: It all
worked out for the best.

273
00:10:49,320 --> 00:10:50,990
The law would never
have been able to give

274
00:10:51,030 --> 00:10:52,960
the punishment he deserved.

275
00:10:52,990 --> 00:10:54,960
There was no better outcome.

276
00:10:55,000 --> 00:10:58,930
Hayato: I-I never really
got along with my dad

277
00:10:58,970 --> 00:11:00,700
when he was still with us,

278
00:11:00,740 --> 00:11:04,370
but, even so,
I never thought i’d lose him.

279
00:11:04,410 --> 00:11:06,710
I wanted justice
for my dad’s death.

280
00:11:06,740 --> 00:11:11,510
i wanted someone
to bring his killer to justice.

281
00:11:13,750 --> 00:11:18,250
( Kira screams )

282
00:11:18,290 --> 00:11:20,490
Reimi: Remember now,
yoshikage Kira?

283
00:11:20,520 --> 00:11:23,390
That’s how your life
was ripped away from you.

284
00:11:23,420 --> 00:11:24,890
Funny how memory works!

285
00:11:24,930 --> 00:11:27,260
kira: I’ve had
just about enough of your games!

286
00:11:27,300 --> 00:11:28,430
Who or what are you?!

287
00:11:30,770 --> 00:11:32,300
Reimi: I’m evidence.

288
00:11:32,330 --> 00:11:34,440
15 years ago,
you didn’t have a stand

289
00:11:34,470 --> 00:11:36,540
that could make
all of your victims disappear.

290
00:11:36,570 --> 00:11:40,340
That’s why, when I was murdered,
it was front-page news.

291
00:11:40,380 --> 00:11:41,740
( Kira gasps )

292
00:11:41,780 --> 00:11:43,610
reimi: Tell me,
does this gash on my back

293
00:11:43,650 --> 00:11:44,880
look familiar to you?

294
00:11:44,910 --> 00:11:46,880
since I was
your very first victim,

295
00:11:46,920 --> 00:11:48,950
maybe you forgot
to cut off my hands!

296
00:11:48,980 --> 00:11:51,850
i guess i’m just
not that memorable to you, huh?

297
00:11:51,890 --> 00:11:54,660
Kira: That’s right. It’s you.

298
00:11:54,690 --> 00:11:57,790
of course.
You’re reimi sugimoto.

299
00:11:59,090 --> 00:12:00,530
Tell me right now what you’ve

300
00:12:00,560 --> 00:12:03,530
been planning here
for the past 15 years!

301
00:12:03,570 --> 00:12:04,530
Huh?

302
00:12:04,570 --> 00:12:05,800
Hold on.

303
00:12:05,830 --> 00:12:07,370
What exactly do you get

304
00:12:07,400 --> 00:12:09,470
out of showing off
your disgusting wound

305
00:12:09,500 --> 00:12:11,840
and revealing
your true identity to me?

306
00:12:11,870 --> 00:12:14,680
Now wait just a moment.
Is this the place

307
00:12:14,710 --> 00:12:17,950
where one shouldn’t look
over their shoulder or else?

308
00:12:17,980 --> 00:12:19,550
( Reimi gasps )

309
00:12:19,580 --> 00:12:21,850
Kira: My old man once said,

310
00:12:21,880 --> 00:12:23,620
hidden somewhere in this town

311
00:12:23,650 --> 00:12:25,950
is a passage
for the souls of the dead.

312
00:12:25,990 --> 00:12:29,760
He told me to never look back
if I ever found myself there.

313
00:12:29,790 --> 00:12:32,430
To do so would invite
an unspeakable power

314
00:12:32,460 --> 00:12:34,560
that would drag you
into an abyss of misery.

315
00:12:34,600 --> 00:12:36,730
- ( Reimi gasps )
- Kira: Now, it’s just a hunch,

316
00:12:36,760 --> 00:12:39,530
but I get the feeling
you only showed me your back

317
00:12:39,570 --> 00:12:41,470
in order to lure me
in front of you

318
00:12:41,500 --> 00:12:43,100
so i’d play
into your ghostly hands

319
00:12:43,140 --> 00:12:44,110
and turn around.

320
00:12:44,140 --> 00:12:45,540
( Reimi gasps )

321
00:12:45,570 --> 00:12:47,010
Kira: You were
trying to trick me,

322
00:12:47,040 --> 00:12:49,610
weren’t you,
my spectral strumpet?

323
00:12:49,640 --> 00:12:52,410
Why don’t you look for me? Hmm?

324
00:12:52,450 --> 00:12:55,020
I would love to see
what happens.

325
00:12:55,050 --> 00:12:57,690
Now let’s have us a look.

326
00:12:57,720 --> 00:12:58,890
Turn that pretty little head!

327
00:12:58,920 --> 00:13:00,520
Reimi: Oh, please.
Did you think

328
00:13:00,560 --> 00:13:02,590
I wouldn’t prepare for you
pulling a stunt like this?

329
00:13:02,620 --> 00:13:05,490
- ( Kira gasps )
- Reimi: You’re so predictable.

330
00:13:05,530 --> 00:13:07,600
We’ve been waiting for 15 years.

331
00:13:07,630 --> 00:13:10,930
that was way more
than enough time to prepare.

332
00:13:10,970 --> 00:13:11,930
Kira: "We"?

333
00:13:11,970 --> 00:13:14,700
( Arnold growls )

334
00:13:14,740 --> 00:13:16,770
Reimi: Yeah! Good boy, Arnold!

335
00:13:16,800 --> 00:13:18,910
( Kira yelps )

336
00:13:18,940 --> 00:13:20,510
( Gasps )

337
00:13:20,540 --> 00:13:23,410
♪

338
00:13:23,440 --> 00:13:25,810
What?! ( Screams )

339
00:13:25,850 --> 00:13:29,920
Reimi: Yoshikage Kira, your hour
of reckoning has arrived.

340
00:13:29,950 --> 00:13:33,050
kira: Disgusting!
What are these putrid things?

341
00:13:33,090 --> 00:13:34,520
Deadly queen!

342
00:13:34,560 --> 00:13:36,860
Make whatever this is explode!

343
00:13:39,490 --> 00:13:41,160
Oh, god, no.

344
00:13:41,200 --> 00:13:42,800
Where are they
going to take me?!

345
00:13:42,830 --> 00:13:44,200
Say something, please!

346
00:13:44,230 --> 00:13:46,570
i have to know
where they’re taking me!

347
00:13:46,600 --> 00:13:48,740
What are they going to do?!
Reimi!

348
00:13:48,770 --> 00:13:51,010
Reimi: Don’t know. Although...

349
00:13:51,040 --> 00:13:53,880
I doubt you’ll be living
in peace and tranquility.

350
00:13:54,940 --> 00:13:59,950
( Kira screams )

351
00:14:05,050 --> 00:14:06,990
♪

352
00:14:13,730 --> 00:14:15,730
Reimi: Now, at long last,

353
00:14:15,760 --> 00:14:19,930
we can finally pass on together.

354
00:14:29,780 --> 00:14:32,980
Koichi: What?! Are you
really leaving us, reimi?

355
00:14:33,010 --> 00:14:35,050
Surely it wouldn’t hurt anything

356
00:14:35,080 --> 00:14:36,820
if you stayed
a little while longer.

357
00:14:36,850 --> 00:14:39,850
I mean, you’ve been like
a guardian angel to this town.

358
00:14:39,890 --> 00:14:42,090
I can’t imagine
life here without you!

359
00:14:42,120 --> 00:14:43,890
Please, you have to stay!

360
00:14:43,930 --> 00:14:45,530
Reimi: Koichi,
you’re very sweet,

361
00:14:45,560 --> 00:14:47,060
but Arnold and I have done

362
00:14:47,100 --> 00:14:48,930
everything we set out
to accomplish here.

363
00:14:48,960 --> 00:14:51,900
the time’s come
for us to leave morioh.

364
00:14:51,930 --> 00:14:54,040
That’s how it has to be.

365
00:14:54,070 --> 00:14:56,570
so, little Rohan,
do you think you’re gonna cry

366
00:14:56,600 --> 00:14:58,970
after we’ve gone off
to the great beyond?

367
00:14:59,010 --> 00:15:00,380
( Rohan chuckles )
In your dreams.

368
00:15:00,410 --> 00:15:02,880
what reason
would I have to miss you?

369
00:15:02,910 --> 00:15:06,210
You died 15 years ago,
making you a distant memory.

370
00:15:06,250 --> 00:15:07,450
I’ve said this before,

371
00:15:07,480 --> 00:15:09,480
but spirits
should really just let go.

372
00:15:09,520 --> 00:15:12,190
Haunting the world of the living
is so out of style.

373
00:15:12,220 --> 00:15:14,420
A soul’s final resting place
isn’t here with us,

374
00:15:14,460 --> 00:15:17,090
but exploring
the uncharted afterlife.

375
00:15:17,130 --> 00:15:18,090
( Koichi groans )

376
00:15:18,130 --> 00:15:20,260
Rohan: Uh, hmph.

377
00:15:20,300 --> 00:15:21,800
( Koichi growling )

378
00:15:21,830 --> 00:15:24,830
( Rohan sighs )

379
00:15:24,870 --> 00:15:26,430
Fine! I’ll say it, all right?!

380
00:15:26,470 --> 00:15:29,100
But i’m only doing so because
i’ll never see you again!

381
00:15:29,140 --> 00:15:30,440
- I’ll miss you!
- ( Koichi laughs )

382
00:15:30,470 --> 00:15:33,140
Rohan: Of course
I don’t want you to go!

383
00:15:33,170 --> 00:15:34,440
( Reimi chuckles )

384
00:15:34,480 --> 00:15:36,380
( Arnold whimpers )

385
00:15:36,410 --> 00:15:37,550
Josuke: Yo.

386
00:15:39,850 --> 00:15:42,480
Koichi: Hey! You’re all here!

387
00:15:42,520 --> 00:15:44,550
Yukako: So it’s all over, reimi?

388
00:15:44,590 --> 00:15:47,560
koichi: Oh, wow!
Looks like everyone showed up!

389
00:15:47,590 --> 00:15:49,390
Mikitaka: We’ve all
come to say goodbye.

390
00:15:49,420 --> 00:15:51,430
♪

391
00:15:51,460 --> 00:15:53,060
( Reimi gasps )

392
00:15:53,090 --> 00:15:54,560
You guys.

393
00:15:54,600 --> 00:15:56,230
josuke:
It feels weird to say this

394
00:15:56,260 --> 00:15:58,470
to the dearly departed,
but take care of yourself.

395
00:15:58,500 --> 00:16:00,100
okuyasu: See you
on the other side, ’kay?

396
00:16:00,130 --> 00:16:01,540
( Mr. Nijimura gurgles )

397
00:16:01,570 --> 00:16:04,340
Joseph: You’re an extraordinary
young woman, dear.

398
00:16:04,370 --> 00:16:06,270
( Reimi whimpers )

399
00:16:11,380 --> 00:16:12,850
Koichi: Oh, reimi,

400
00:16:12,880 --> 00:16:14,820
thank you so much
for all you’ve done!

401
00:16:14,850 --> 00:16:17,590
You saved this little town when
it needed a savior the most!

402
00:16:17,620 --> 00:16:19,520
reimi: Thank you
for saying that, koichi,

403
00:16:19,550 --> 00:16:23,160
but we saved morioh,
all of us together.

404
00:16:23,190 --> 00:16:24,930
Joseph: As long
as we draw breath,

405
00:16:24,960 --> 00:16:29,060
no one here today will ever
forget you or your bravery.

406
00:16:29,100 --> 00:16:30,370
Reimi: Thank you, all.

407
00:16:30,400 --> 00:16:31,930
That means the world.

408
00:16:31,970 --> 00:16:33,500
So long, my friends. Be well.

409
00:16:33,530 --> 00:16:35,300
( Rohan sighs )

410
00:16:35,340 --> 00:16:37,140
Koichi: So long, reimi.

411
00:16:37,170 --> 00:16:38,340
Godspeed.

412
00:16:48,550 --> 00:16:50,520
Rest easy.

413
00:16:54,090 --> 00:16:56,520
Shinobu: Where is he?
it’s so late.

414
00:16:56,560 --> 00:16:59,060
I guess he’s working overtime.

415
00:16:59,090 --> 00:17:01,060
It would have been nice
if he called, though.

416
00:17:01,100 --> 00:17:03,060
( Hayato gasping )

417
00:17:03,100 --> 00:17:07,000
shinobu: Oh, hayato,
you haven’t touched your food.

418
00:17:07,040 --> 00:17:08,900
hurry up
before it gets cold.

419
00:17:08,940 --> 00:17:11,210
If you’re waiting for me,
i’ll eat when dad gets home.

420
00:17:11,240 --> 00:17:14,140
( Hayato gasping )

421
00:17:15,440 --> 00:17:17,480
Shinobu: Uh, hayato?

422
00:17:17,510 --> 00:17:20,220
Hayato: It’s okay, mom.
I’ll wait with you.

423
00:17:20,250 --> 00:17:24,190
When dad gets home, we’ll all
sit down and eat together,

424
00:17:24,220 --> 00:17:27,220
’cause that’s
what a family does, right?

425
00:17:27,260 --> 00:17:29,320
Shinobu: Sure.

426
00:17:29,360 --> 00:17:31,060
Say, am I imagining things,

427
00:17:31,090 --> 00:17:34,260
or have you
gotten taller lately?

428
00:17:34,300 --> 00:17:36,600
Koichi: When all
was said and done,

429
00:17:36,630 --> 00:17:40,030
our little morioh
wasn’t the town it used to be.

430
00:17:40,070 --> 00:17:43,440
A monster named yoshikage Kira
swept in like a plague

431
00:17:43,470 --> 00:17:45,340
and had his way
with our beloved home.

432
00:17:45,370 --> 00:17:48,680
Hayato’s mother will no doubt
wait for her husband

433
00:17:48,710 --> 00:17:50,410
until the end of time,

434
00:17:50,450 --> 00:17:53,180
and shigechi’s parents
will never stop waiting

435
00:17:53,210 --> 00:17:55,320
for their special
little man to return.

436
00:17:55,350 --> 00:17:59,190
Whether a son, daughter,
brother, or sister,

437
00:17:59,220 --> 00:18:03,060
kira’s victims belong to parents
who will never give up hope,

438
00:18:03,090 --> 00:18:05,060
and yet that hope

439
00:18:05,090 --> 00:18:07,960
will only cause their pain
to grow deeper.

440
00:18:08,000 --> 00:18:11,470
The question is, what can
we do to lessen this burden?

441
00:18:11,500 --> 00:18:14,940
Will a vile past
consume our future,

442
00:18:14,970 --> 00:18:18,440
or will we be able to forge
ahead, unfettered by fear?

443
00:18:18,470 --> 00:18:20,480
I wish I could say.

444
00:18:20,510 --> 00:18:23,480
Joseph: How ’bout it, jotaro?

445
00:18:23,510 --> 00:18:25,580
You worried about
what might happen

446
00:18:25,610 --> 00:18:27,280
when we leave this place?

447
00:18:27,320 --> 00:18:29,020
Jotaro: I am, just a bit.

448
00:18:29,050 --> 00:18:31,320
Joseph: Because of all this,
we’ve had the chance

449
00:18:31,350 --> 00:18:34,490
to see how capable
josuke and his friends are,

450
00:18:34,520 --> 00:18:37,630
and there’s one thing I can say
with absolute certainty.

451
00:18:37,660 --> 00:18:40,100
The young people
living in this town

452
00:18:40,130 --> 00:18:41,460
are heroes one and all,

453
00:18:41,500 --> 00:18:44,370
and each one of them
possesses a heart of gold.

454
00:18:44,400 --> 00:18:46,030
They’ve the same
righteous hearts

455
00:18:46,070 --> 00:18:48,270
we witnessed
on our journey to Egypt.

456
00:18:48,300 --> 00:18:50,240
They carry a spirit of radiance

457
00:18:50,270 --> 00:18:53,210
that will fight for true justice
above all else.

458
00:18:53,240 --> 00:18:56,440
I see it in josuke,
as well as the others.

459
00:18:56,480 --> 00:18:59,510
Morioh’s in good hands
with them.

460
00:18:59,550 --> 00:19:03,180
As long as they’re here,
we have nothing to worry about.

461
00:19:03,220 --> 00:19:04,690
Josuke: Hey, old man!

462
00:19:04,720 --> 00:19:07,390
Don’t just stand there gawkin’!
Answer me!

463
00:19:07,420 --> 00:19:10,360
Joseph: Well, then, guess it’s
time for me to say goodbye

464
00:19:10,390 --> 00:19:13,360
to a great son who’s made
his father so very proud.

465
00:19:13,390 --> 00:19:15,200
Josuke: Hey, remember
that picture of mom

466
00:19:15,230 --> 00:19:16,600
I gave you a while ago?

467
00:19:16,630 --> 00:19:18,230
You don’t still have it,
do you?

468
00:19:18,270 --> 00:19:19,400
Joseph: ’course I do!

469
00:19:19,430 --> 00:19:21,500
I put it in my wallet
for safekeeping,

470
00:19:21,540 --> 00:19:23,340
just like you told me to! Hah!

471
00:19:23,370 --> 00:19:25,740
Since I can’t tell her
in person, i’ll tell you.

472
00:19:25,770 --> 00:19:28,280
i wish her
all the happiness in the world.

473
00:19:28,310 --> 00:19:32,550
Josuke: So, funny thing
about that picture I gave you.

474
00:19:32,580 --> 00:19:35,050
I decided to hang on to a piece.

475
00:19:36,120 --> 00:19:38,690
Shining diamond!

476
00:19:38,720 --> 00:19:39,750
Joseph: Eh?

477
00:19:39,790 --> 00:19:42,120
Josuke: Oh, wow,

478
00:19:42,160 --> 00:19:43,290
you shouldn’t have!

479
00:19:43,320 --> 00:19:45,190
Though i’ll take it
if you insist!

480
00:19:45,230 --> 00:19:47,760
We’ll just call this gift
16 years of back allowance!

481
00:19:47,800 --> 00:19:50,430
Besides, think about what
your better half would say

482
00:19:50,470 --> 00:19:52,170
if you took that picture
home with you!

483
00:19:52,200 --> 00:19:54,440
joseph: Who does
that cocky punk think he is?

484
00:19:54,470 --> 00:19:57,110
Jotaro: I’m starting to see
that golden spirit, old man,

485
00:19:57,140 --> 00:19:59,770
and he’s seeing it
all the way to the bank.

486
00:19:59,810 --> 00:20:02,380
Josuke: You take
good care of yourself!

487
00:20:02,410 --> 00:20:04,410
( Joseph growls )

488
00:20:04,450 --> 00:20:05,580
( Chuckles )

489
00:20:05,610 --> 00:20:07,780
- ( Jotaro chuckles )
- ( Baby coos )

490
00:20:07,820 --> 00:20:11,090
Koichi: The invisible baby’s
mother was never found,

491
00:20:11,120 --> 00:20:13,190
so Joseph joestar
Rose to the occasion

492
00:20:13,220 --> 00:20:15,290
and began an adventure
as a new dad.

493
00:20:15,320 --> 00:20:19,360
Jotaro kujo finally finished
a doctoral thesis he began

494
00:20:19,390 --> 00:20:22,230
on a species of starfish
he found on a beach in morioh,

495
00:20:22,260 --> 00:20:24,570
earning him his phd.

496
00:20:24,600 --> 00:20:27,400
( Tomoko groans )
Damn that josuke!

497
00:20:27,440 --> 00:20:28,740
He’s always coming in here

498
00:20:28,770 --> 00:20:31,210
and eating all my food
like he owns the place!

499
00:20:31,240 --> 00:20:34,610
( Groans )
I’ll just drink his juice!

500
00:20:34,640 --> 00:20:36,180
Yukako: Koichi!

501
00:20:36,210 --> 00:20:38,480
- koichi: Huh?
- Yukako: Sorry i’m late!

502
00:20:38,510 --> 00:20:42,180
I was making bento boxes for us
and lost track of the time.

